### Register candidate
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "candidate@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "role": "CANDIDATE"
}

### Login
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "candidate@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### Create interview
POST http://localhost:8080/api/interviews
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "candidateId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "role": "Java Backend Engineer"
}

### Submit interview
POST http://localhost:8080/api/interviews/{{interviewId}}/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "answers": [
    { "question": "Explain Kafka consumer groups.", "answer": "Consumer groups allow horizontal scaling where each partition is consumed by one member in the group." },
    { "question": "How do you handle idempotency?", "answer": "Persist an idempotency key and make retries return the same logical outcome." }
  ]
}

### Fetch evaluation
GET http://localhost:8080/api/evaluations/interviews/{{interviewId}}

### Create checkout session
POST http://localhost:8080/api/payments/checkout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "planCode": "PRO"
}

### Complete mock payment callback
POST http://localhost:8080/api/payments/callbacks/mock
Content-Type: application/json
Idempotency-Key: demo-callback-001

{
  "checkoutSessionId": "{{checkoutSessionId}}"
}
